Connection Architecture
The connection between your remote Mucho3D server and local Blender typically works in one of two ways: 
The AI Client as the Bridge: Your AI interface (like the Claude Desktop App or Cursor) acts as the middleman. It connects to the Remote Ollama/MCP server via the internet and then sends commands to your Local Blender over a local network port (default is often 9876). 
